cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.MS 

The paper deals with statistical properties and applications of wireless communication systems, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT), Communications (cs.COMM), and Networking (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the performance of radio frequency and optical wireless communication systems, which falls under the Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper presents analytical expressions for the joint probability density function, cumulative distribution function, and moment generation function, which are related to the Mathematical Statistics (cs.MS) sub-category.
